               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary>A partial copy of the Mitākṣarā copied for Burnouf in 1832-1833 by Śorakkuḍi [Tamil Curakkuṭi] Kṛṣṇaśasāstrin. It contains the Vyavahārādhyāya only, under the name  Vyavahārakāṇḍa, apparently complete, up to Strīsaṃgrahaṇaprakaraṇam (see intertitle) and Prakīrṇakaprakaraṇam (but no intertitle).      </summary>
                  
